Experience Senior Financial Accountant – Global Infrastructure & Hardware Team – APAC Google June 2014  – Present (1 year 3 months) As part of my role on the Global Infrastructure & Hardware Team, I have been responsible for completing the monthly financial accounting activites for capital expenditure and equipment and related operating expenses for the APAC entity portfolio. 

These duties include: 

- Taking ownership of day-to-day financial accounting duties (e.g.preparing, reviewing and/or approving monthly capitalisations, retirements, cost adjustments and intercompany entries coming from the business, depreciation expense analysis, preparation of accruals, prepayments, amortisations, adjustments and reclass entries); 

- Participating in systems and process improvements projects to ensure that our systems continue to be robust enough to manage the changing environment in which we operate; 

- The performance of monthly and quarterly variance analysis and reporting to the US based consolidations team; 

- Managing information requests and organising communications to and from the local compliance teams, other finance functional teams and internal and external audit; 

- Playing a key role in maintaining the integrity of internal controls around such areas as the preparation and independent review of balance sheet account reconciliations; and 

- Participating in the joint management of relationships and deliverables from our global shared services vendors. Financial Accountant – US GAAP – APAC Google November 2012  –  June 2014  (1 year 8 months) During my my time with Google, working as a Financial Accountant on the US GAAP team, I have performed the financial accounting function for facilities, travel and entertainment, legal and finance related operating expenses for the APAC entity portfolio. 

As part of this role, I have been responsible for: 

- Taking ownership of day-to-day financial accounting duties (e.g. Preparation of accruals, prepayments, amortisations, lease straight lines, adjustments and reclass entries); 

- The performance of monthly and quarterly variance analysis and reporting to the US based consolidations team; 

- Managing information requests and organising communications to and from the local compliance teams, other finance functional teams and internal and external audit; 

- Playing a key role in maintaining the integrity of internal controls around such areas as the preparation and independent review of balance sheet account reconciliations; and 

- Participating in the joint management of relationships and deliverables from our global shared services vendors. 

Outside the scope of my ordinary responsibilities, I have also been involved with: 

- Becoming the Finance Disaster Recovery Communications Project Manager for APAC; and 

- Co-presenting on an Accounting Concepts and Applications course for our Finance Operations functional team. Assistant Manager - Audit & Advisory KPMG Australia June 2008  –  October 2012  (4 years 5 months) • Nov-11 – Oct-12 – Assistant Manager 
• Jan-10 – Oct-11 – Senior Accountant 
• Jun-08 – Dec-09 – Accountant 

During my four and a half years with KPMG, I worked in the Audit and Advisory business of the Private Enterprise Division. Working predominantly on external statutory financial statement and prudential compliance audits, I have been involved in all aspects of the audit process, from initial risk assessment and planning, to controls and substantive audit testing, through to completion, financial statements and board reporting. 

I have also had exposure to a number of internal audit and other assurance engagements, working closely with client business partners and management to help better understand the existing control environment and deficiencies, and to identify areas to mitigate control and business risk. 

Additionally, I spent a three month period in KPMG’s business advisory and tax division, working predominantly on the provision of account maintenance and financial statement preparation services for a number of our self managed superannuation fund clients. 

My industry experience includes clients operating in the following sectors: 
- Financial Services (Building Societies/Credit Unions); 
- Manufacturing;  
- Local Government; 
- Mining and Mineral Exploration; and 
